div.p:
I Find it related by Herodotus, how Cyrus intending to Conquer Scythia, came to a great broad River which hindred his journey, whereupon he bethought himſelf of this policy,
to cut it, and divide it into many parts and ſluces, and ſo made it paſſable for all his Army; The like policy hath the Divel now uſed amongſt us, bringing his power of darkeneſs to invade and over-run us, and finding his paſſage ſtopped by the flowing ſtreames of love and concord, he hath put in practice to ſeperate and divide us into many parts and factions: we are become like rivelets not joyned together, but every man running his owne way, ſo that the Divel may now ford us, and faſhion us, and turne us as he pleaſe. My bowels, my bowels, I am pained at my very heart, my heart maketh a noiſe in me, I cannot hold my peace, becauſe thou haſt heard ô my ſoul, the ſound of the Trumpet, the alarum of wars: Deſtruction upon deſtruction is cryed, for the whole land is ſpoyled;
ſuddenly are my tents ſpoiled, and my curtaines in a moment; How long ſhall I ſee the ſtandard, and hear the ſound of the Trumpet Ier. 4.19, 20, 21.?
